keywords sacrifice
---
Syntax: sacrifice <item>
        sacrifice <item> <deity>

Sacrifices an item to a deity in exchange for gold or alignment adjustment.
The amount of gold received depends on the item's value and your character's
level.

Deity options:
  (none)            -- Neutral sacrifice, gold only.
  <goodgodname>     -- Sacrifice to the good deity; shifts alignment toward
                       good. Anti-evil items produce a larger alignment shift.
  <evilgodname>     -- Sacrifice to the evil deity; shifts alignment toward
                       evil. Anti-good items produce a larger alignment shift.
  judge             -- Pays off your criminal sentence (PLR_KILLER/PLR_THIEF
                       flags). Reduces sentence; when fully paid, criminal
                       flags are removed. Unique and clan items cannot be
                       used for fine payment.

Restrictions:
  - Cannot sacrifice yourself.
  - Most objects must be in your inventory and droppable.
  - Corpses of NPCs can be sacrificed; PC corpses cannot.
  - Quest items and items flagged as NO_SAC cannot be sacrificed.
  - Some room types prohibit sacrifice.

See also: junk donate gold worth
